39. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 2019092662
T1  - Development and validation of an instrument to measure the worries related to polycystic ovary syndrome in Iranian women, A Mixed Method Study Running title: Worries instrument of polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Nikbakht R.
A1  - Salajegheh Z.
A1  - Ahmadi A.
A1  - Bafghi Z.R.
A1  - Alidousti K. 
AO  - Nikbakht, Roya; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9684-8529
AO  - Salajegheh, Zahra; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7653-1172
AO  - Ahmadi, Atefeh; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5366-9849
AO  - Bafghi, Zahra Ramazanian; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0815-9484
AO  - Alidousti, Katayoun; ORCID: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1206-4912
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - PCOS is a chronic disease related to reproduction. Affected women have worries and concerns about possible complications or physical, psychological and social problems related to this disease in the future. Therefore, this study was done with the aim of developing and validating a questionnaire special for the worries of women with poly cystic ovary syndrome in Iranian Women. An initial six-factor instrument was constructed based on this psychometric study. The face validity and content validity of the instrument were measured. The factor structure of the instrument was investigated by exploratory factor analysis (EFA) among 357 PCOS patients. To determine the underlying factor structure, confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) was performed in this population. The internal and external reliability of the instrument was evaluated. The questionnaire's draft version consisted of 36 questions with 6 domains. Questions with a high validity were selected using CVR and CVI to assess the content validity (0.93 and 0.98, respectively). KMO was 0.72 in this study, and Bartlett's test was significant (P-value < 0.001). and the overall Cronbach's alpha was 0.77. PCFI was 0.625, the CFI index was 0.8, and the SRMR was 0.09. After checking face validity and factor analysis, the number of questions was decreased to 17 and the domains to 4. It seems that the questionnaire had acceptable reliability and validity and can be used as an efficient tool for measuring polycystic ovary patients' worries.Copyright © 2022, Anka Publishers. All rights reserved.
