59. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 2019883622
T1  - Prevalent endocrinological abnormalities in adolescence
T3  - Alteraciones endocrinologicas prevalentes en la adolescencia
A1  - Moreno L.R.
A1  - Pita O.M.
A1  - Ugalde-Abiega B.
A1  - Perez A.M. 
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Puberty is the stage of life in which an individual goes from childhood to adulthood. This period is critical as there are numerous physiological, psychoemotional, and social changes that can lead to concerns and diseases, some with long-term repercussions in adulthood. In this update, we will discuss the problems of this age, such as disorders during puberty, obesity as a worldwide public health problem, and diseases associated with insulin resistance such as metabolic syndrome or polycystic ovary syndrome. We will address type 1 diabetes mellitus in terms of the need for a transitional consultation to avoid the risk of acute decompensations. We will discuss gender identity and its approach in this age and the endocrinological aspects of eating disorders. Lastly, there is a miscellaneous section where we will make reference to the peculiarities of adolescence in diseases such as growth or thyroid disorders.Copyright © 2022
