93. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 639717797
T1  - SHC INHIBITORY DRUGS DIRECTLY TARGET HEPATIC STELLATE CELLS AND REDUCE FIBROSIS IN VIVO
T3  - Annual Meeting of the American Association for the Study of Liver Diseases, AASLD 2022. Virtual.
A1  - Jiang J.X.
A1  - Tomilov A.
A1  - Torok N.J.
A1  - Cortopassi G. 
Y1  - 2022//
N2  - Background: We previously showed that Shc expression increased in NASH. Mice with hepatocyte-specific Shc knockdown were protected from fast food diet, and a repurposed Shc inhibitor idebenone rescued mice from NASH diets. However, the mechanistic role of Shc in fibrosis has not been specified. We hypothesized that Shc mediates stellate cell (HSC) activation and proliferation contributing to liver fibrosis. Our aims are 1. To elucidate Shc's role in HSC function; 2. To evaluate the antifibrotic efficacy of idebenone and novel Shc inhibitors NCE3 and NCE5. Method(s): Primary mouse HSCs were culture activated with/ without Shc inhibitors idebenone, NCE3 and NCE5. Shc and fibrosis markers (alphaSMA, pcollagen 1, and TGFbeta) were evaluated with qPCR. LX2 cells treated with TGFbeta, with/without Shc inhibitors were also evaluated for the fibrosis gene expression. Cell proliferation was analyzed in wild type and ShcKO HSCs. LX-2 cells were treated with PDGF with/without the inhibitors, and proliferation was evaluated. The anti-fibrotic efficacy of Shc inhibitors was evaluated in 3 models. First, the mice were on MCD diet for 5 weeks with either idebenone, NCE3 or NCE5 20 mg/kg daily oral 5 weeks long. Next, mice were on fast food diet for 12 weeks and idebenone 6 weeks starting in the middle of feeding, representing a therapeutic arm. Third, 4-week old Mdr2KO mice were given idebenone or NCE3 for 2 weeks. Fibrosis was assessed with qPCR, picrosirius red and hydroxyproline assays. Result(s): Shc expression significantly increased in culture-activated HSCs and this was abolished by idebenone, and novel Shc inhibitors NCE3 and NCE5. Meanwhile the fibrosis genes decreased significantly by the drugs. The drugs also inhibited the fibrotic markers in the TGFbeta-activated LX-2 cells. ShcKO HSCs proliferated less than wild type cells. PDGF-induced cell proliferation was blunted by the inhibitors. In addition, Shc inhibitors significantly improved liver fibrosis in the MCD model, fast food model, as well as Mdr2KO mice. Conclusion(s): We have demonstrated that Shc expression increases in active HSCs. Shc inhibition reduces HSC activation and proliferation in vitro. We further show that pharmacological Shc suppression significantly inhibits liver fibrosis in the MCD, fast food and Mdr2KO mouse models. Thus, it appears that Shc is a novel drug target for liver fibrosis, and the therapeutic mechanism appears to be suppression of HSC activation and proliferation.
