N2  - Early multimodal oral administration of analgesics is one the components of enhanced recovery after surgery protocols. As effective as parenteral analgesia, Patient-Controlled oral analgesia (PCOA) allows ambulation of parturients whishing to care for their newborns. Oral analgesics available for pain relief after caesarean section have to be evaluated in terms of efficacy and safety in the setting of breast-feeding.Copyright © 2020 Elsevier Masson SAS
