T1  - Hypothalamic Amenorrhea
T2  - Contemporary Endocrinology
A1  - Kanj R.V.
A1  - Gordon C.M. 
Y1  - 2019//
N2  - Functional hypothalamic amenorrhea (FHA) is a condition characterized by suppression of the hypothalamic-pituitary-ovarian (HPO) axis, with low circulating estradiol and chronic anovulation. FHA does not have an organic cause and is, therefore, a diagnosis of exclusion. This diagnosis often occurs in the setting of low energy availability and can be associated with excessive exercise, dieting, and/or stress. FHA can have acute and chronic medical sequelae secondary to hypoestrogenism. Management options include nutritional rehabilitation, mental health support such as cognitive behavior therapy (CBT), and short-term hormone replacement as part of a multidisciplinary integrated approach.Copyright © 2019, Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
