N2  - The proceedings contain 1086 papers. The topics discussed include: three-arm RCT: vaginal only progesterone is inferior, but vaginal plus intramuscular (IM) progesterone every third day is equivalent, to daily IM progesterone for vitrified-warmed blastocyst transfer in terms of live birth; joint impact of maternal age and BMI on cumulative live birth following in vitro fertilization; advances in permanent contraception: intrauterine administration of combined polidocanol plus doxycycline foam stimulates permanent fallopian tube occlusion in baboons; testosterone treatment alters placental angiogenesis, inflammation, and oxidative stress throughout gestation in a sheep model of polycystic ovary syndrome; endometriosis and risk of adverse maternal and pregnancy outcomes; disparities in access to infertility care in the united states: results from the national health and nutrition examination survey, 2013-2016; infertility and health-related quality of life in veterans; African American patients experience reduced pregnancy, higher pregnancy loss, and lower live birth from IVF embryo transfers despite producing more oocytes and more transfer quality embryos than Caucasian patients; knowledge, attitudes, and perceptions of infertility: a national survey; lower gestational age and increased risk of preterm birth associated with singleton live birth resulting from in vitro fertilization (IVF) among African American versus comparable Caucasian women; and disordered eating pathology in polycystic ovary syndrome: prevalence and predictors in a longitudinal cohort.
