330. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 621458938
T1  - Characteristic MRI findings in hemifacial spasm correlated with operative findings
T3  - 12th Asian-Oceanian Congress of Neuroradiology and the 21st Symposium Neuroradiologicum. Taipei Taiwan (Republic of China).
A1  - Shen C.-Y.
A1  - Li C.-S.
A1  - Tyan Y.-S.
A1  - Weng J.-C.
A1  - Chou M.-C. 
Y1  - 2018//
N2  - Introduction: About 80-90% hemifacial spasm (HFS) results from vascular compression of the affected facial nerve. Microvascular decompression (MVD) appears to be the most popular and effective surgical treatment but still with about 10% failure and recurrence rate. MRI can help to detect the offender vessels that compress the affected facial nerve and preoperative planning. In this study, we retrospective comparison of pre-MVD MRI and operative findings and analysis potential patterns of posterior circulations that causing HFS. Method(s): HFS patient underwentMVD fromMay 2014 to May 2017 in Chung Shan Medical University Hospital were retrospective reviewed. Comparisons between pre-MVDMRimages (both 3D-TOF and 3D-SPACE, using 3-TeslaMRI) and operative findingwere performed. The offender vessels were defined from both MRI and operative finding). AICA-PICA dominance, VA dominance, PcoA dominance and BA curvature were recorded and analyzed the association with offender vessels. Result(s): Total 51 HFS patients (M/F=14/37, mean age=55.2 years old) were included in this study. 70% of the offender vessels were AICA and 75% of AICA compression were dominant AICA (ipsilateral PICA hypoplasia). 27% of the offender vessels showed inconsistent betweenMRI and operative finding.DominantVAand dominant PcomAwere not associated with offender vessels (P>0.05). The direction (R/L) of BA curvature showed significant associated with contralateral offender vessels (P<0.05). Conclusion(s): Our results indicated thatAICAs were themajor offender vessels inHFS.Variable AICA-PICA dominance may influence the accuracy to detect offender vessel during operation. The direction of BA curvature may have associated with affected side of HFS..
