796. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 32780598
T1  - Psychopharmacology and women
A1  - Miller L.J. 
Y1  - 2001//
N2  - Sex differences in pharmacokinetics and reproductive changes should be taken into account in order to optimize therapeutic effects and minimize side effects when prescribing psychotropic medications for women. This article summarizes clinically relevant data about topics such as pharmacokinetic differences; the effects of the menstrual cycle, pregnancy, and breast-feeding; and considerations for optimal use of antidepressant, mood-stabilizing, and antipsychotic medications for women.
